There are Attack Types and Attack Resistances. Attack a target with low resistance to your unit's Attack Type.
Generate bonus damage with a Chain by repeatedly using the same Attack Type on an enemy.
Learn about Cast Targeting, Viewpoint Display, and Camera Rotation.
Understand the basics of TP-Consuming Abilities, AP-Consuming Abilities, and Limit Bursts.
Every unit in your party has Affinity for an element. Check each unit's Affinity before attacking.
Attacks have Elemental Types, while Units have Elemental Resistances. Attack a target with an element to which it has low Resistance.
Generate an Elemental Chain by repeatedly attacking an enemy with abilities of the same element.
Learn how to avoid and prevent Status Ailments.
Opponents can have high Resistance to certain Status Ailments. Try inflicting a target with Status Ailments to which it has low Resistance.
Learn about height difference and the range of arching-shot fire for bows.
AGI determines how quickly a unit's turn will come. Meanwhile, ending a turn without acting will cause that unit's next turn to come more quickly. Use these tactics to your advantage in battle.
A countdown begins when the unit is KO'd. At count 0, the KO'd unit will retreat from the stage, so be careful.
Be sure to pick up Item Drops from KO'd enemies, as well as Crystals that appear after units have retreated.
Equip Espers, fill the Evocation Gauge, and activate powerful Evocation Magic.
